Comparative effect of clinidipine and quinapril on left ventricular mass in mild essential hypertension. The aim of this study was to compare the regressive effect of clinidipine on left ventricular mass (LVM) with that of quinapril. Sixty patients with mild essential hypertension aged more than 39 years were randomly allocated to two groups to receive cilnidipine (10 mg n = 30) or quinapril (10 mg